content: Hey! I've been feeling really stressed lately with work. My boss keeps piling on more projects and I can barely keep up.
I love coffee though - it's the only thing getting me through these long days. I probably drink like 4 cups a day lol
My dog Max has been such a comfort. He's a golden retriever and just the sweetest thing. When I come home stressed, he always knows.
I'm thinking about starting to meditate. Everyone says it helps with anxiety but I've never been good at sitting still.
Oh and I HATE when people are late. It's such a pet peeve of mine. Like, just respect other people's time, you know?
I've been binge-watching The Office again. It's my comfort show. I've probably seen it 5 times already.
My sister is getting married next month! I'm excited but also nervous about the speech I have to give.
I really want to learn guitar. I bought one last year but it's just been sitting in the corner. I need to actually commit to it.
Work was brutal today. I had back-to-back meetings from 9am to 5pm. I didn't even have time for lunch.
I'm a software engineer btw, working at a startup in San Francisco. It's exciting but exhausting.
Sometimes I wonder if I should just quit and travel the world. Life's too short to be this stressed all the time.
But then I remember I have student loans to pay off. Ugh, adulting is hard.
I love hiking though! Went to Yosemite last weekend and it was amazing. Nature really helps me decompress.
I'm trying to eat healthier. I've been ordering too much takeout and I can feel it affecting my energy levels.
My best friend Sarah is moving to New York next month. I'm really going to miss her. We've been friends since college.
I hate crowded places. Like, I'll avoid going to the mall on weekends at all costs. Too many people, too much noise.
I'm reading this book on stoicism. It's really making me think about how I react to stress.
My goal is to get promoted to senior engineer by next year. I've been working really hard for it.
I love rainy days. There's something cozy about staying inside with a good book and some tea.
My parents keep asking when I'm going to settle down and get married. I'm only 27! There's no rush.
I've been journaling every morning. It helps me organize my thoughts and set intentions for the day.
I really dislike small talk. Like, let's have real conversations or nothing at all.
I'm thinking about adopting another dog to keep Max company. But I'm worried about the responsibility.
I love cooking! It's therapeutic for me. I made homemade pasta last night and it turned out great.
I get anxious before big presentations. Even though I've done tons of them, the nerves never go away.
My dream is to eventually start my own company. I have so many ideas but I'm scared of failing.
I hate when people interrupt me when I'm talking. It's so disrespectful.
I'm trying to be more mindful and present. I spend too much time on my phone and it's affecting my relationships.
I love learning new things. I'm always taking online courses or reading about something new.
Overall, I'm grateful for my life even though it's stressful. I have good friends, a job I mostly enjoy, and Max. That's what matters.
